org.apache.beam.it.mongodb

Class MongoDBResourceManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.beam.it.testcontainers.TestContainerResourceManager<MongoDBContainer>
      • org.apache.beam.it.mongodb.MongoDBResourceManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.beam.it.common.ResourceManager

    public class MongoDBResourceManager
extends TestContainerResourceManager<MongoDBContainer>
implements org.apache.beam.it.common.ResourceManager
    Client for managing MongoDB resources.

    The class supports one database and multiple collections per database object. A database is created when the first collection is created if one has not been created already.

    The database name is formed using testId. The database name will be "{testId}-{ISO8601 time, microsecond precision}", with additional formatting.

    The class is thread-safe.
